FIX: Completely remove ALL Confluent Kafka custom resources
Run this to show ALL objects in the namespace:
Shellkubectl get all -n kafkaShow more lines
Then delete EVERYTHING:
Shellkubectl delete all --all -n kafkaShow more lines
But this is not enough, because Confluent operator uses Custom Resources (CRs) stored under API groups ‚Äî NOT shown under "all".
You must delete them too:

STEP 1 ‚Äî Detect all existing API objects in the namespace
Run:
Shellkubectl api-resources --verbs=list --namespaced -o name | \xargs -n 1 kubectl get -n kafka --ignore-not-foundShow more lines
This will reveal hidden CRs such as:

kafkas.platform.confluent.io
controllers.platform.confluent.io
connectors.platform.confluent.io
zookeepers.platform.confluent.io

Even if CRDs are removed, these objects remain and cause pods to respawn.

STEP 2 ‚Äî Delete all Confluent custom objects forcibly
Run:
Shellkubectl delete kafka --all -n kafka --ignore-not-foundkubectl delete controller --all -n kafka --ignore-not-foundkubectl delete zookeeper --all -n kafka --ignore-not-foundkubectl delete ksql --all -n kafka --ignore-not-foundkubectl delete connect --all -n kafka --ignore-not-foundkubectl delete replicator --all -n kafka --ignore-not-foundShow more lines
These are all CFK resource types.

STEP 3 ‚Äî Delete the namespace ENTIRELY
This is the cleanest fix.
Shellkubectl delete namespace kafkaShow more lines
Wait until it is fully removed:
Shellkubectl get nsShow more lines
Then recreate a clean namespace:
Shellkubectl create namespace kafkaShow more lines

STEP 4 ‚Äî Install Bitnami Kafka cleanly
Shellhelm install kafka bitnami/kafka -n kafkaShow more lines

üü¢ EXPECTED OUTPUT
After reinstall:
Shellkubectl get pods -n kafkaShow more lines
You should see:
kafka-0          Running
kafka-1          Running
kafka-2          Running
zookeeper-0      Running
zookeeper-1      Running
zookeeper-2      Running

NO MORE:
kafka-controller-0
kafka-controller-1
kafka-controller-2


